{
    "code": "02", 
    "data": "بِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْمِ \nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اِنّي اَسْاَلُكَ بِرَحْمَتِكَ الَّتِيْ وَسِعَتْ كُلَّ شَيْءٍ \nO My God! I beseech You through (the medium of) Your Mercy which encompasses all things,\nوَ بِقُوَّتِكَ الَّتِيْ قَهَرْتَ بِها كُلَّ شَيْءٍ وَ خَضَعَ لَها كُلُّ شَيْءٍ \nand through (the medium of) Your Might which overpowers all things, to which all things submit and compared to which all things are humble,\nوَ ذَلَّ لَها كُلُّ شَيْءٍ وَ بِجَبَرُوْتِكَ الَّتِيْ غَلَبْتَ بِها كُلَّ شَيْءٍ \nand through (the medium of) Your Power through which You have conquered all things,\nوَ بِعِزَّتِكَ الَّتِيْ لَا يَقُومُ لَهَا شَيْءٌ وَ بِعَظَمَتِكَ الَّتِيْ مَلَاَتْ كُلَّ شَيْءٍ \nand through (the medium of) Your Greatness against which nothing can stand up (or can rise), and through (the medium of) Your Grandeur which prevails upon all things,\nوَ بِسُلْطانِكَ الَّذي عَلٰي كُلَّ شَيْءٍ وَ بِوَجْهِكَ الْبَاقِيْ بَعْدَ فَنَاءِ كُلِّ شَيْءٍ \nand through (the medium of) Your Own self which will continue existing when all things will pass away (cease to exist),\nوَ بِاَسْمَائِكَ الَّتِيْ مَلَاَتْ اَرْكَانَ كُلِّ شَيْءٍ وَ بِعِلْمِكَ الَّذِيْ اَحَاطَ بِكُلِّ شَيْءٍ \nand through (the medium of) Your Names (attributes) which manifest Your Power over all things,\nوَ بِنُوْرِ وَجْهِكَ الَّذِيْ اَضَاءَ لَهٗ كُلُّ شَيْءٍ \nand through (the medium of) Your Knowledge which pervades all things,\nيَا نُوْرُ يَا قُدُّوْسُ يَا اَوَّلَ اْلَاوَّلِيْنَ وَ يَا آخِرَ اْلآخِرِيْنَ \nO You (who are) the Light, O You (who are) the most Holy, O You who existeth before the foremost things (from time without beginning), O You who shalt exist after the last things will cease to exist (You are Eternal – no beginning and no end).\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِيَ الذُّنُوْبَ الَّتِيْ تَهْتِكُ الْعِصَمَ \nO my Lord! forgive my such sins as would disgrace virtue;\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اغْفِـرْ لِيَ الذُّنُوْبَ الَّتِيْ تُنْزِلُ النِّقَمَ \nO my Lord! forgive my such sins as would bring down retribution (from the Heavens);\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِيَ الذُّنُوْبَ الَّتِيْ تُغَيِّـرُ النِّعَمَ \nO my Lord! forgive my such sins as would change prosperity and happiness (into afflictions and sorrows);\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِيَ الذُّنُوْبَ الَّتِيْ تَحْبِسُ الدُّعَاءَ \nO my Lord! forgive my such sins as would intercept my invocations and prayers;\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِيَ الذُّنُوْبَ الَّتِيْ تَقْطَعُ الرَّجَآءَ \nO my Lord! forgive my such sins as would suppress hope;\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِيَ الذُّنُوْبَ الَّتِيْ تُنْزِلُ الْبَلَاءَ \nO my Lord! Forgive my such sins as would bring down afflictions;\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِيْ كُلَّ ذَنْبٍ اَذْنَبْتُهٗ وَ كُلَّ خَطِيْئَة اَخْطَاْتُهَا \nO my Lord! forgive all the sins that I have committed and all the vices that I am guilty of.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اِنِّيْ اَتَقَرَّبُ اِلَيْكَ بِذِكْرِكَ وَ اَسْتَشْفِعُ بِكَ اِلٰى نَفْسِكَ \nO my Lord! I endeavour to achieve Your favour through Your praises and invocations to You; I pray to You to intercede Yourself on my behalf;\nوَ اَسْاَلُكَ بِجُوْدِكَ اَنْ تُدْنِيَنِيْ مِنْ قُرْبِكَ \nI entreat of Thine benevolence to grant me Your nearness, \nوَ اَنْ تُوْزِعَنِيْ شُكْرَكَ وَ اَنْ تُلْهِمَنِيْ ذِكْرَكَ \nto bestow on me the quality of feeling (truly) grateful to You and to inspire me to keep on remembering and invoking You.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اِنّي اَسْاَلُكَ سُؤَالَ خَاضِعٍ مُتَذَلِّلٍ خَاشِعٍ \nO my Lord! I entreat You begging submissively, humbly and meekly \nاَنْ تُسَامِحَنِيْ وَ تَرْحَمَنِيْ وَ تَجْعَلَنِيْ بِقِسْمِكَ رَاضِيَا قَانِعًا \nto treat me mercifully, to take pity on me, to make me contented, satisfied and pleased with what is allotted to me by You, \nوَ فِيْ جَمِيْعِ اْلَاحْوَالِ مُتَوَاضِعًا اَللّٰهُمَّ وَ اَسْاَلُكَ سُؤَالَ مَنِ اشْتَدَّتْ فَاقَتُهٗ \nand to keep me gentle and modest in all circumstances (in all phases of life). Lord! I beg You as one who is passing through extreme privations \nوَ اَنْزَلَ بِكَ عِنْدَ الشَّدَائِدِ حَاجَتَهٗ وَ عَظُمَ فِيْمَا عِنْدَكَ رَغْبَتُهٗ\nand in his misery supplicates his needs to You, and (as one) whose cravings are great for the things which are Thine.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ عَظُمَ سُلْطَانُكَ وَ عَلَا مَكَانُكَ وَ خَفِيَ مَكْرُكَ وَ ظَهَرَ اَمْرُكَ \nLord! Great is Your Kingdom, exalted is Your Place, inscrutable are Your Ways, evident is Your Authority, \nوَ غَلَبَ قَهْرُكَ وَ جَرَتْ قُدْرَتُكَ وَ لَا يُمْكِنُ الْفِرَارُ مِنْ حُكُومَتِكَ \noverwhelming is Your Might, ever-operating (acting) is Your Power and no escape is possible from Your Domain.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ لَا اَجِدُ لِذُنُوْبِيْ غَافِرًا وَ لَا لِقَبَائِحِيْ سَاتِرًا \nLord! except You I do not find any one (so kind as) to pardon my sins, to conceal my degradations (despicable actions) \nوَ لَا لِشَيْءٍ مِنْ عَمَلِيَ الْقَبِيْحِ بِالْحَسَنِ مُبَدِّلًا غَيْرَكَ \nand to divert me (my mind) from vices to virtues.\nلَا اِلٰـهَ اِلَّا اَنْتَ سُبْحَانَكَ وَ بِحَمْدِكَ ظَلَمْتُ نَفْسِيْ \nThere is no God but You, Glory and praise be to You, I have harmed myself (by foul deeds), \nوَ تَجَرَّأْتُ بِجَهْلِيْ وَ سَكَنْتُ اِلٰى قَدِيْمِ ذِكْرِكَ لِيْ وَ مَنِّكَ عَلَيَّ \nI have boldly taken to sins and vices as I was ignorant (of Your Wrath and Power) and confident of my past prayers and invocations and Your (constant) mercies and blessings on me (which I took for granted).\nاَللّٰهُمَّ مَوْلَايَ كَمْ مِنْ قَبِيْحٍ سَتَرْتَهٗ وَ كَمْ مِنْ فَادِحٍ مِنَ الْبَلَاءِ اَقَلْتَهٗ \nMy God! O my Lord! How many of my vices have You covered (from public gaze), how many calamities (descending upon me) have You reduced the severity of; \nوَ كَمْ مِّنْ عِثَارٍ وَّ قَيْتَهٗ وَ كَمْ مِّنْ مَكْرُوْهٍ دَفَعْتَهٗ \nhow many of my mistakes have You corrected, how many misfortunes have You averted (from me), \nوَ كَمْ مِّنْ ثَنَآءٍ جَمِيْلٍ لَّسْتُ اَهْلًا لَهٗ نَشَرْتَهٗ \nhow many elegant praises have You allowed to be propagated about me which I did not merit!\nاَللّٰهُمَّ عَظُمَ بَلَآئِيْ وَ اَفْرَطَ بِيْ سُوْٓ ءُ حَالِيْ وَ قَصُرَتْ بِيْ اَعْمَالِيْ \nO my Lord! my trials and misfortunes are great, and my sorrows and sufferings are intense, and my good deeds are few, \nوَ قَعَدَتْ بِيْ اَغْلَالِىْ وَ حَبَسَنِيْ عَنْ نَفْعِيْ بُعْدُ اَمَلِيْ \nand my manacles (liabilities and responsibilities) lie heavily upon me. And inordinate (remote) desires keep me away even from lawful gains.\nوَ خَدَعَتْنِيْ الدُّنْيَا بِغُرُوْرِهَا وَ نَفْسِيْ بِجِنَايَتِهَا وَ مِطَالِيْ \nThe world has deceived me with its vanities and my mind has deceived me with dishonesty and procrastination.\nيَا سَيِّدِيْ فَاَسْاَلُكَ بِعِزَّتِكَ اَنْ لَا يَحْجُبَ عَنْكَ دُعَآئِيْ سُوْٓءُ عَمَلِيْ وَ فِعَالِيْ \nTherefore, my Lord, I implore You in the name of Your greatness not to let my sins and vices hinder my prayers from access to Your realm, \nوَ لَا تَفْضَحْنِيْ بِخَفِيِّ مَا اطَّلَعْتَ عَلَيْهِ مِنْ سِرِّىْ \nand not to disgrace me by exposing my (hidden) sins and vices of which You have knowledge, \nوَ لَا تُعَاجِلْنِيْ بِالْعُقُوْبَةِ عَلٰى مَا عَمِلْتُهُ فِيْ خَلَوَاتِيْ \nand not to hasten Your retribution for the vice’s I have committed secretly \nمِنْ سُوْٓ ءِ فِعْلِيْ وَ اِسَآئَتِيْ وَ دَوَامِ تَفْرِيْطِيْ وَ جَهَالَتِيْ \nand which were due to evil-mindedness, sinfulness, ignorance, \nوَ كَثْرَةِ شَهْوَاتِيْ وَ غَفْلَتِيْ وَ كُنِ اللّٰهُمَّ بِعِزَّتِكَ لِيْ فِيْ كُلِّ اْلَاحْوَالِ رَؤُوْفًا \nlustfulness and negligence. So my Lord (I crave You) for the sake of Your greatness under all (those) circumstances before giving \nوَّ عَلَيَّ فِيْ جَمِيْعِ اْلاُمُوْرِ عَطُوْفًا \nand under all conditions be merciful unto me.\nاِلٰهِيْ وَ رَبِّيْ مَنْ لِيْ غَيْرُكَ اَسْاَلُهٗ كَشْفَ ضُرِّيْ وَ النَّظَرَ فِيْ اَمْرِيْ \nO my God! have I any one besides You, O my Lord! to whom can I turn in my hour of afflictions to relieve me of my sorrows and to put my affairs in order!\nاِلٰهِيْ وَ مَوْلَايَ اَجْرَيْتَ عَلَيَّ حُكْمًا نِاتَّبَعْتُ فِيْهِ هَوٰى نَفْسِيْ \nMy God! My Master! Your commandments came into force for me (to obey) but I followed (evil) intentions of my (warped) mind, \nوَ لَمْ اَحْتَرِسْ فِيْهِ مِنْ تَزْيِيْنِ عَدُوِّيْ فَغَرَّنِيْ بِمَا اَهْوٰى \nand I heeded not those commandments) on account of allurements staged by my enemy who deceived me through my passions (evil desires), and my ill luck also favoured him (my enemy) in this.\nوَ اَسْعَدَهٗ عَلٰى ذٰلِكَ الْقَضَآءُ فَتَجَاوَزْتُ بِمَا جَرٰى عَلَيَّ مِنْ ذٰلِكَ \nThus I transgressed some of the bonds set by You (for human freedom) \nبَعْضَ حُدُوْدِكَ وَ خالَفْتُ بَعْضَ اَوَامِرِكَ \nand I disobeyed some of Your commands.\nفَلَكَ الْحَمْدُ عَلَيَّ فِيْ جَمِيْعِ ذٰلِكَ وَ لَا حُجَّةَ لِيْ فِيْمَا جَرٰى عَلَيَّ فِيْهِ قَضَآؤُكَ \nPraise be to You, my Lord! You have proof against me in all these matters, and I have no argument (no reasoning) to protest against Your Judgement \nوَ اَلْزَمَنِيْ حُكْمُكَ وَ بَلَآؤُكَ وَ قَدْ اَتَيْتُكَ \nand Your Orders and Afflictions (sent down by You).\nيَآ اِلٰهِيْ بَعْدَ تَقْصِيْرِيْ وَ اِسْرَافِيْ عَلٰى نَفْسِيْ مُعْتَذِرًا نَادِمًا مُنْكَسِرًا \nI return to You, my Lord, after having committed the sins of omission and commission against myself apologetic, repentant, \nمُسْتَقِيْلًا مُسْتَغْفِرًا مُنِيْبًا مُقِرًّا مُّذْعِنًا مُعْتَرِفًا \nbroken-hearted, imploring forgiveness, begging pardon (for my sins) confessing (my vices), submissive and admitting (my faults).\nلَّا اَجِدُ مَفَرًّا مِمَّا كَانَ مِنِّيْ وَ لَا مَفْزَعًا اَتَوَجَّهُ اِلَيْهِ فِيْ اَمْرِيْ \nI see no escape from that which has been done by me, and I find no refuge to which I may turn \nغَيْرَ قَبُوْلِكَ عُذْرِيْ وَ اِدْخَالِكَ اِيَايَ فِيْ سَعَةِ رَحْمَتِكَ \nexcept that You mayest (kindly) accept my excuse (plea). And allow me to enter the realm of Your Mercy.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ فَاقْبَلْ عُذْرِيْ وَ ارْحَمْ شِدَّةَ ضُرِّيْ وَ فُكَّنِيْ مِنْ شَدِّ وَثَاقِيْ \nO my Lord! Accept my apology, and have pity on my intense sufferings, and set me free from the strong fetters (put on by my evil deeds).\nيَا رَبِّ ارْحَمْ ضَعْفَ بَدَنِيْ وَ رِقَّةَ جِلْدِيْ وَدِقَّةَ عَظْمِيْ \nLord! Have mercy on the weakness of my body, and on the tenderness of my skin and on the brittleness of my bones.\nيَا مَنْۢ بَدَاَ خَلْقِيْ وَ ذِكْرِيْ وَ تَرْبِيَتِيْ وَ بِرِّىْ وَ تَغْذِيَتِيْ هَبْنِيْ \nO You! Who originated my creation (and then) granted me fame and honour, (Who) arranged for my upbringing and ensured my welfare and made provisions for my food, as You have been generous to me\nلِاِبـْتِدَآءِ كَرَمِكَ وَ سَالِفِ بِرِّكَ بِيْ \nfrom the very beginning of my life, please continue Your Favours and Blessings as before.\nيَا اِلٰهِيْ وَسَيِّدِيْ وَ رَبِّيْ اَ تُرَاكَ مُعَذِّبِيْ بِنَارِكَ بَعْدَ تَوْحِيْدِكَ \nO my God! O my Master! Will You see me punished in Your hell after I have faithfully believed in Your Unity?\nوَ بَعْدَ مَا انْطَوٰى عَلَيْهِ قَلْبِيْ مِنْ مَعْرِفَتِكَ \nAnd when my heart has been truly and loyally filled with knowledge about You?\nوَ لَهِجَ بِهٖ لِسَانِيْ مِنْ ذِكْرِكَ وَ اعْتَقَدَهُ ضَمِيْرِيْ مِنْ حُبِّكَ \nAnd when my tongue has persistently praised You and repeated Your name, and I have conscientiously, faithfully, and constantly loved You, \nوَ بَعْدَ صِدْقِ اعْتِرَافِيْ وَ دُعَآئِيْ خَاضِعًا لِرُبُوْبِيَّتِكَ \nand after sincere confessions (of my sins and vices) and after the moving and humble entreaties made by me?\nهَيْهَاتَ اَنْتَ اَكْرَمُ مِنْ اَنْ تُضَيِّعَ مَنْ رَّبَّيْتَهٗ \nNo, My Lord! such an action is far from You, You are far too kind and generous to lay waste one whom You have nourished, maintained and supported, \nاَوْ تُبَعِّدَ مَنْ اَدْنَيْتَهٗ اَوْ تُشَرِّدَ مَنْ اٰوَيْتَهٗ \nor drive away from Yourself one whom You have kept under Your protection. Or to scare away one whom You have given shelter,\nاَوْ تُسَلِّمَ اِلَى الْبَلَآءِ مَنْ كَفَيْتَهٗ وَرَحِمْتَهٗ \nor to abandon one to afflictions and trials whom You have protected and have shown Kindness and Mercy.\nوَ لَيْتَ شِعْرِىْ يَا سَيِّدِيْ وَ اِلٰهِيْ وَ مَوْلَايَ \nO my Master! My God and my Lord! I can never believe \nاَ تُسَلِّطُ النَّارَ عَلٰى وُجُوْهٍ خَرَّتْ لِعَظَمَتِكَ سَاجِدَةً \nthat You will empower the fire (of hell) to burn faces which have submissively bowed in prostration before Your Greatness.\nوَّ عَلٰى اَلْسُنٍ نَطَقَتْ بِتَوْحِيْدِكَ صَادِقَةً وَ بِشُكْرِكَ مَادِحَةً\nAnd (You will burn in the fire of hell) the tongues which have sincerely declared Your Unity and have been always thankful (for kindness and Mercy).\nوَّ عَلٰى قُلُوْبٍ نِاعْتَرَفَتْ بِاِلٰهِيَّتِكَ مُحَقِّقَةً \nAnd (You will permit the fires of hell to consume) the hearts which have acknowledge Your Divinity with conviction.\nوَّ عَلٰى ضَمَآئِرَ حَوَتْ مِنَ الْعِلْمِ بِكَ حَتّٰى صَارَتْ خَاشِعَةً \nAnd (you will allow to be cremated in hell) the minds which have gathered such knowledge about You as to feel humble and submissive before You.\nوَّ عَلٰى جَوَارِحَ سَعَتْ اِلٰى اَوْطَانِ تَعَبُّدِكَ طَآئِعَةً وَ اَشَارَتْ بِاِسْتِغْفَارِكَ مُذْعِنَةً\nAnd (You will consent to consumption by fire in hell) of bodies whose endeavours, wherever they lived, were directed towards obedience and service to You and which have exerted themselves with deserving humility to seek Your Forgiveness. \nمَا هٰكَذَا الظَّنُّ بِكَ وَ لَآ اُخْبِرْنَا بِفَضْلِكَ عَنْكَ يَا كَرِيْمُ \nSuch an attitude can never be expected of You (O my God), nor Your Kindness and Grace will allow me to hold such a belief, O Generous One!\nيَا رَبِّ وَ اَنْتَ تَعْلَمُ ضَعْفِيْ عَنْ قَلِيْلٍ مِّنْۢ بَلَآءِ الدُّنْيَا وَ عُقُوْبَاتِهَا \nO Lord! You are aware of my weakness to bear even minor afflictions and calamities of this world or their consequences, \nوَ مَا يَجْرِيْ فِيْهَا مِنَ الْمَكَارِهِ عَلٰى اَهْلِهَا عَلٰى اَنَّ ذٰلِكَ بَلَآءٌ وَ مَكْرُوْهٌ قَلِيْلٌ مَّكْثُهٗ يَسِيْرٌ بَقَاؤُهٗ قَصِيْرٌ مُّدَّتُهٗ \nand also of adversities which befall men inhabiting this world, though all those trials and afflictions are momentary, short lived and transient.\nفَكَيْفَ احْتِمَالِيْ لِبَلَآءِ اْلآخِرَةِ وَ جَلِيْلِ وُقُوْعِ الْمَكَارِهِ فِيْهَا \n(Lord!) How can I bear the retributions and the punishments of the hereafter which are enormous \nوَ هُوَ بَلَآءٌ تَطُوْلُ مُدَّتُهٗ وَ يَدُوْمُ مَقَامُهٗ وَ لَا يُخَفَّفُ عَنْ اَهْلِهٖ \nand of intensive sufferings, of prolonged period or of perpetual duration, and which shall never be reduced or alleviated \nلِاَنَّهٗ لَا يَكُوْنُ اِلَّا عَنْ غَضَبِكَ وَ اْنتِقَامِكَ وَ سَخَطِكَ \nfor those who deserve these punishments; because those retributions will be the result of Your Wrath, Your Punishment and Your Anger \nوَ هٰذَا مَا لَا تَقُوْمُ لَهُ السَّمٰوَاتُ وَ اْلَارْضُ \nwhich neither the heavens nor the earth can withstand and bear.\nيَا سَيِّدِيْ فَكَيْفَ لِيْ وَ اَنَا عَبْدُكَ الضَّعِيْـفُ الـذَّلِيْـلُ الْحَقِيْـرُ الْمِسْكِيْـنُ الْمُسْتَكِيْنُ \nO my Lord! How can I, a weak, insignificant, humble, poor and destitute creature of You bear them?\nيَا اِلٰهِيْ وَ رَبِّيْ وَ سَيِّدِيْ وَ مَوْلَايَ لِاَيِّ اْلاُمُوْرِ اِلَيْكَ اَشْكُوْ \nO my God! My Lord! My King! and my Master! about how many things (of hell) shall I complain to You and about how many shall I bewail and weep;\nوَ لِمَا مِنْها اَضِجُّ وَ اَبْكِيْ لِاَلِيْمِ الْعَذَابِ وَ شِدَّتِهٖ \nAbout the pain and pangs of punishment and its intensity or about the prolongation of sufferings and their duration.\nاَمْ لِطُوْلِ الْبَلَآءِ وَ مُدَّتِه فَلَئِنْ صَيَّرْتَنِىْ لِلْعُقُوْبَاتِ مَعَ اَعْدَائِكَ \nBecause, my Lord! if You will submit me to the penalties (of Hell!) together with Your enemies \nوَ جَمَعْتَ بَيْنِيْ وَ بَيْنَ اَهْلِ بَلَآئِكَ وَ فَرَّقْتَ بَيْنِيْ وَ بَيْنَ اَحِبَّآئِكَ وَ اَوْلِيَآئِكَ \nand cast me with those who deserved those punishments, and if You will separate me from Your friends and from those who love You,\nفَهَبْنِيْ يَا اِلٰـهِىْ وَ سَيِّدِيْ وَ مَوْلَايَ وَ رَبِّيْ صَبَرْتُ عَلٰى عَذَابِكَ فَكَيْفَ اَصْبِرُ عَلٰى فِرَاقِكَ\nI realise that You have the right to do so, but my God, my Lord and my master! (please let me submit that) though I may patiently bear thy punishments, how can I calmly accept the separation from You (Your Grace and Mercy?)\nوَ هَبْنِيْ (يَا اِلٰهِيْ) صَبَرْتُ عَلٰى حَرِّ نَارِكَ \n (And) please Lord, let me submit that though I may patiently endure the scorching fire of Your hell, \nفَكَيْفَ اَصْبِرُ عَنِ النَّظَرِ اِلٰى كَرَامَتِكَ \nyet how can I resign myself to the denial of Your pity and clemency; \nاَمْ كَيْفَ اَسْكُنُ فِي النَّارِ وَ رَجَآئِيْ عَفْوُكَ \nhow can I remain in the fire (of hell) while I have hopes of Your forgiveness?\nفَبِعِزَّتِكَ يَا سَيِّدِىْ وَ مَوْلَايَ اُقْسِمُ صَادِقًا لَّئِنْ تَرَكْتَنِيْ نَاطِقًا \nTruly do I swear by Your honour, O my Lord and O my Master that, if You will allow my power of speech to be retained by me, \nلَاَضِجَّنَّ اِلَيْكَ بَيْنَ اَهْلِهَا ضَجِيْجَ اْلآمِلِيْنَ \nI will, from amongst the inmates (of hell), cry out unto You with the cry of those who have faith in Your Kindness and Compassion.\nوَ لَاَصْرُخَنَّ اِلَيْكَ صُرَاخَ الْمَسْتَصْرِخِيْنَ \nAnd I shall loudly beseech You for help and mercy with the voice of those who shriek for succour, \nوَ لَاَبْكِيَنَّ عَلَيْكَ بُكَاءَ الْفَاقِدِيْنَ وَ لَاُنَادِيَنَّكَ \nand I shall lament like those who are desperately in need of Your help, and I shall keep on calling unto You; \nاَيْنَ كُنْتَ يَا وَلِيَّ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ يَا غَايَةَ آمَالِ الْعَارِفِيْنَ يَا غِيَاثَ الْمُسْتَغِيْثِيْنَ \n“Where are You, O Friend of the believers! O (You who are) the last hope and resort of those who have faith in Your Clemency and Kindness; O the Helper of those who seek Your help! \nيَا حَبِيْبَ قُلُوْبِ الصَّادِقِيْنَ وَ يَا اِلٰهَ الْعَالَمِيْنَ اَفَتُرَاكَ\nO (You who are) dear to the hearts of those who truly believe in You! and O (You who are) the Lord of the Universe.”\nسُبْحانَكَ يَا اِلٰهِىْ وَ بِحَمْدِكَ تَسْمَعُ فِيْهَا صَوْتَ عَبْدٍ مُسْلِمٍ \nSee You my plight, O my Lord! Glory and Praise be unto You, You will be hearing from inside hell the voice of Your humble creature (myself) \nسُجِنَ فِيْهَا بِمُخَالَفَتِهٖ وَ ذَاقَ طَعْمَ عَذَابِهَا بِمَعْصِيَتِهٖ\nwho is thrown in there in punishment for his disobedience and who tastes the chastisements (of hell) for his sins, \nوَ حُبِسَ بَيْنَ اَطْبَاقِهَا بِجُرْمِهٖ وَ جَرِيْرَتِهٖ\nand who is confined within its layers because of his crimes and vices \nوَ هُوَ يَضِجُّ اِلَيْكَ ضَجِيْجَ مُؤَمِّلِ لِرَحْمَتِكَ \nand who cries to You (my Lord) with the voice of one who has faith in Your Mercy \nوَ يُنَادِيْكَ بِلِسَانِ اَهْلِ تَوْحِيْدِكَ وَ يَتَوَسَّلُ اِلَيْكَ بِرُبُوْبِيَّتِكَ \nand calls out to You in the language of those who believes in Your Unity, and who seeks Your Grace and Help (with a firm belief) in Your Authority and Lordship.\nيَا مَوْلَايَ فَكَيْفَ يَبْقٰى فِي الْعَذَابِ وَ هُوَ يَرْجُوْ مَا سَلَفَ مِنْ حِلْمِكَ \nO My Lord! How could he remain in the abode of chastisement who puts his confidence in Your past Forbearance and Clemency?\nاَمْ كَيْفَ تُؤْلِمُهُ النَّارُ وَ هُوَ يَامُلُ فَضْلَكَ وَ رَحْمَتَكَ \nHow could the fire of hell hurt him who has hope in Your Kindness and Compassion?\nاَمْ كَيْفَ يُحْرِقُهٗ لَهِيْبُهَا وَ اَنْتَ تَسْمَعُ صَوْتَهٗ وَ تَرٰى مَكَانَهٗ \nHow could the flames of hell burn anybody while You hearest his voice and seest his plight?\nاَمْ كَيْفَ يَشْتَمِلُ عَلَيْهِ زَفِيْرُهَا وَ اَنْتَ تَعْلَمُ ضَعْفَهٗ \nHow could the roaring (fires) of hell terrify anyone whose weaknesses You are aware of?\nاَمْ كَيْفَ يَتَقَلْقَلُ بَيْنَ اَطْبَاقِهَا وَ اَنْتَ تَعْلَمُ صِدْقَهٗ \nHow can he, whose sincerity is known to You, be tossed into the layers of hell?\nاَمْ كَيْفَ تَزْجُرُهٗ زَبَانِيَتُهَا وَ هُوَ يُنَادِيْكَ يَا رَبَّهٗ \nHow can the flames of hell torture him who keeps on calling You as his Lord?\nاَمْ كَيْفَ يَرْجُوْ فَضْلَكَ فِيْ عِتْقِهِ مِنْهَا فَتَتْرُكُهٗ فِيْهَا \nHow is it possible that while a person has faith in Your Kindness and Mercy to set him free from hell, You shouldst abandon him there?\nهَيْهَاتَ مَا ذٰلِكَ الظَّنُ بِكَ وَ لَا الْمَعْرُوْفُ مِنْ فَضْلِكَ \nNo, my Lord! nobody can believe You to be thus, neither Your Grace has such a reputation; nor have You through Goodness \nوَ لَا مُشْبِهٌ لِّمَا عَامَلْتَ بِهِ الْمُوَحِّدِيْنَ مِنْ بِرِّكَ وَ اِحْسَانِكَ \nand Clemency ever dealt in this way with those who have faith in Your Unity.\nفَبِالْيَقِيْنِ اَقْطَعُ لَوْلَا مَا حَكَمْتَ بِهٖ مِنْ تَعْذِيْبِ جَاحِدِيْكَ \nI am positively certain (my Lord) that have You not ordained punishment for those who disbelieve in You, \nوَ قَضَيْتَ بِهٖ مِنْ اِخْلَادِ مُعَانِدِيْكَ لَجَعَلْتَ النَّارَ كُلَّهَا بَرْدًا وَّ سَلَامًا \nand have You not decreed Your enemies to remain in hell, You would have turned the fire of hell cold and pleasant, \nوَّ مَا كَانَتْ لِاَحَدٍ فِيْهَا مَقَرًّا وَّ لَا مُقَامًا لٰكِنَّكَ تَقَدَّسَتْ اَسْمَآؤُكَ \nand it (the burning and blazing hell) would never have become an abode of or a halting place for any one.\nاَقْسَمْتَ اَنْ تَمْلَاَهَا مِنَ الْكَافِرِيْنَ مِنَ الْجِنَّةِ وَ النَّاسِ اَجْمَعينَ \nBut, sanctified be Your names, You have worn to fill hell with all the disbelievers from amongst the Jinns and mankind \nوَ اَنْ تُخَلِّدَ فِيْهَا الْمُعَانِدِيْنَ وَ اَنْتَ جَلَّ ثَنَآؤُكَ قُلْتَ مُبْتَدِئًا \nand to throw in it (hell) all Your enemies (and to keep them there) forever. You, exalted be Your praise, hath said in the beginning \nوَّ تَطَوَّلْتَ بِاْلاِنْعَامِ مُتَكَرِّمًا اَفَمَنْ كَانَ مُؤْمِنًا كَمَنْ كَانَ فَاسِقًا لَّا يَسْتَوُؤْنَ \nand out of Your Generosity and Kindness, hath come to the generous decision that faithful followers (of Your Orders) can never be (treated) like those who are sinners.\nاِلٰهِىْ وَ سَيِّدِىْ فَاَسْاَلُكَ بِالْقُدْرَةِ الَّتِىْ قَدَّرْتَهَا \nMy Lord! My Master! I, therefore, implore You by that Power \nوَ بِالْقَضِيَّةِ الَّتِيْ حَتَمْتَهَا وَ حَكَمْتَهَا وَ غَلَبْتَ مَنْ عَلَيْهِ اَجْرَيْتَهَا \nand Might which You possesses and by that faith of Thine (not to treat alike the good and bad) which You have finalised and ordained and thereby hath overpowered those upon whom You have imposed it, \nاَنْ تَهَبَ لِىْ فِىْ هٰذِهِ اللَّيْلَةِ وَ فِيْ هٰذِهِ السَّاعَةِ كُلَّ جُرْمٍ اَجْرَمْتُهٗ \nto forgive tonight and during this very hour all the transgressions that I am guilty of.\nوَ كُلَّ ذَنْۢبٍ اَذْنَبْتُهٗ وَ كُلَّ قَبِيْحٍ اَسْرَرْتُهٗ وَ كُلَّ جَهْلٍ عَمِلْتُهٗ \nAll the sins that I have committed, all the vices that I have kept secret and all the evil deeds that I have done, \nكَتَمْتُهٗ اَوْ اَعْلَنْتُهٗ اَخْفَيْتُهٗ اَوْ اَظْهَرْتُهٗ \nwhich I may have done secretly or openly, and which I may have tried to keep hidden or may have committed publicly, \nوَ كُلَّ سَيِّئَةٍ اَمَرْتَ بِاِثْبَاتِهَا الْكِرَامَ الْكَاتِبِيْنَ الَّذِيْنَ وَكَّلْتَهُمْ \nand all my evil actions that You have ordered the two immaculate (and accurate) Scribes to note down, they are appointed by You to keep a correct record of all of my actions \nبِحِفْظِ مَا يَكُوْنُ مِنِّيْ وَ جَعَلْتَهُمْ شُهُوْدًا عَلَيَّ مَعَ جَوَارِحِيْ \nand to act along with the limbs of my body as witnesses to all of my doings arid beside them all You (my Lord) does, keep a watch over me.\nوَ كُنْتَ اَنْتَ الرَّقِيْبَ عَلَيَّ مِنْ وَّرَآئِهِمْ وَ الشَّاهِدَ لِمَا خَفِيَ عَنْهُمْ \nAnd You knows the things which have been hidden from them, but have through Your Mercy kept my vices secret (from everybody)\nوَ بِرَحْمَتِكَ اَخْفَيْتَهٗ وَ بِفَضْلِكَ سَتَرْتَهٗ وَ اَنْ تُوَفِّرَ حَظِّيْ مِنْ كُلِّ خَيْرٍ اَنْزَلْتَهٗ \nand through Your Kindness drawn a curtain over them. And I pray to You (my Lord) to increase my share in all the good that You do bestow;\nاَوْ اِحْسَانٍ فَضَّلْتَهٗ اَوْ بِرٍّ نَشَرْتَهٗ اَوْ رِزْقٍ بَسَطْتَهٗ اَوْ ذَنْۢبٍ تَغْفِرُهٗ \nand in all the favours that You do grant; all the virtues that You do allow to be known everywhere; all the sustenance and livelihood that You do Distribute (in greater and greater quantities); \nاَوْ خَطَأٍ تَسْتُرُهٗ يَا رَبِّ يَا رَبِّ يَا رَبِّ \nAll the sins that You do forgive and all the vices that You do cover up.\nيَا اِلٰهِيْ وَ سَيِّدِيْ وَ مَوْلَايَ وَ مَالِكَ رِقِّى، يَا مَنْۢ بِيَدِهٖ نَاصِيَتِىْ \nO Lord! O Lord! O Lord! O my God! my Lord! my King! O master of my freedom! O You! who holds my destiny \nيَا عَلِيْمًا بِضُرِّىْ وَ مَسْكَنَتِىْ يَا خَبِيْرًا بِفَقْرِىْ وَ فَاقَتِىْ \nand are aware of my sufferings and my poverty, O You! who knows my destitution and starvation, \nيَا رَبِّ يَا رَبِّ يَا رَبِّ اَسْاَلُكَ بِحَقِّكَ وَ قُدْسِكَ وَ اَعْظَمِ صِفَاتِكَ وَ اَسْمَآئِكَ \nO Lord! O Lord! O Lord! I beseech You by Your Glory and Your Honour, by Your Supremely high attributes and Your Names \nاَنْ تَجْعَلَ اَوْقَاتِيْ مِنَ اللَّيْلِ وَ النَّهَارِ بِذِكْرِكَ مَعْمُوْرَةً \nto make me busy day and night with Your Remembrance, \nوَّ بِخِدْمَتِكَ مَوْصُولَةً وَّ اَعْمَالِىْ عِنْدَكَ مَقْبُوْلَةً \nengaged in serving You (Your Cause) and to let my deeds be such as to be acceptable to You, \nحَتّٰى تَكُوْنَ اَعْمَالِيْ وَ اَوْرَادِىْ كُلُّهَا وِرْدًا وَّاحِدًا \nso much so that all my actions and offerings (prayers) may be transformed into one continuous and sustained effort \nوَّ حَالِىْ فِىْ خِدْمَتِكَ سَرْمَدًا يَا سَيِّدِيْ يَا مَنْ عَلَيْهِ مُعَوَّلِيْ \nand my life may take the form of constant and perpetual service to You (Your Cause). O My Master! O You! on whom I rely,\nيَا مَنْ اِلَيْهِ شَكَوْتُ اَحْوَالِيْ يَا رَبِّ يَا رَبِّ يَا رَبِّ \nO You! unto whom I supplicate about (the miseries and sufferings of) my life. O my Lord! my Lord! my Lord!\nقَوِّ عَلٰى خِدْمَتِكَ جَوَارِحِىْ وَ اشْدُدْ عَلَى الْعَزِيْمَةِ جَوَانِحِيْ \nStrengthen my limbs for Your service and sustain my strength and perseverance to continue it.\nوَ هَبْ لِيَ الْجِدَّ فِيْ خَشْيَتِكَ وَ الدَّوَامَ فِيْ اْلاِتِّصَالِ بِخِدْمَتِكَ \n(Lord) Grant me that I may continuously endeavour to keep Your fear (in my mind) and to be occupied constantly in Your service, \nحَتّٰى اَسْرَحَ اِلَيْكَ فِيْ مَيَادِيْنِ السَّابِقِيْنَ وَ اُسْرِعَ اِلَيْكَ فِي الْبَارِزِيْنَ \ntill I can successfully compete (with those striving) to reach You (Your Grace) faster and quicker than the ones who are in the first rank; \nوَ اَشْتَاقَ اِلٰى قُرْبِكَ فِي الْمُشْتَاقِيْنَ وَ اَدْنُوَ مِنْكَ دُنُوَّ الْمُخْلِصِيْنَ \nand I may hasten with those who eagerly surge to be near You, so that I may be as close to You as those sincere ones who have attained Your Nearness, \nوَ اَخَافَكَ مَخَافَةَ الْمُوْقِنِيْنَ وَ اَجْتَمِعَ فِىْ جِوَارِكَ مَعَ الْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ \nand I may keep on fearing You like those sincere believers who constantly keep Your fear in their minds and thus I may join the assemblage of the faithful (gathered) near You.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ وَ مَنْ اَرَادَنِيْ بِسُوْٓءٍ فَاَرِدْهُ وَ مَنْ كَادَنِيْ فَكِدْهُ \nO Allah, (please) let ill befall on him who, wishes me ill, (please) bring distress to him who plots against me.\nوَ اجْعَلْنِيْ مِنْ اَحْسَنِ عَبِيْدِكَ نَصِيْبًا عِنْدَكَ وَ اَقْرَبِهِمْ مَنْزِلَةً مِنْكَ \nAnd assign unto me a place in Your Presence with the best of Your servants whose place is nearest to You, \nوَ اَخَصِّهِمْ زُلْفَةً لَدَيْكَ فَاِنَّهٗ لَا يُنَالُ ذٰلِكَ اِلَّا بِفَضْلِكَ \nfor verily that position cannot be attained except through Your Favour.\nوَجُدْ لِيْ بِجُوْدِكَ وَ اعْطِفْ عَلَيَّ بِمَجْدِكَ وَ احْفَظْنِيْ بِرَحْمَتِكَ \nLord! Please treat me benevolently and through Your Greatness extend Your Favour towards me, \nوَ اجْعَلْ لِّسَانِىْ بِذِكْرِكَ لَهِجًا وَّ قَلْبِيْ بِحُبِّكَ مُتَـيَّمًا \nand through Your Mercy protect me and let my tongue be constantly busy in Your Remembrance and let my heart be filled with Your Love \nوَّ مُنَّ عَلَيَّ بِحُسْنِ اِجابَتِكَ وَ اَقِلْنِيْ عَثْرَتِيْ وَ اغْفِرْ زَلَّتِيْ \nand be kind to me with Gracious acceptance (of my service and prayers), and weaken the force and intensity of my vices and forgive my evil doings.\nفَاِنَّكَ قَضَيْتَ عَلٰى عِبَادِكَ بِعِبَادَتِكَ وَ اَمَرْتَهُمْ بِدُعَآئِكَ \nFor verily, You have ordained that Your creatures should obey You \nوَ ضَمِنْتَ لَهُمُ اْلاِجَابَةَ فَاِلَيْكَ يَا رَبِّ نَصَبْتُ وَجْهِيْ وَ اِلَيْكَ يَا رَبِّ مَدَدْتُ يَدِيْ \nand have bidden them to pray unto You and have assured their acceptance. So, my Lord! I have fixed my gaze upon You and my Lord! I have extended my hands (in supplications) towards You.\nفَبِعِزَّتِكَ اسْتَجِبْ لِيْ دُعَآئِيْ وَ بَلِّغْنِيْ مُنَايَ وَ لَا تَقْطَعْ مِنْ فَضْلِكَ رَجَآئِيْ \nTherefore, for the sake of Your Honour accept my prayers and allow me to attain my objective; and by Your Favour (I implore You) do not frustrate my hopes, \nوَ اكْفِنِيْ شَرَّ الْجِنِّ وَ اْلاِنْسِ مِنْ اَعْدَآئِيْ \nand throughly protect me from the enmity and malice of my foes, from among the Jinns and mankind.\nيَا سَرِيْعَ الرِّضَا اِغْفِرْ لِمَنْ لَّا يَمْلِكُ اِلَّا الدُّعَآءَ فَاِنَّكَ فَعَّالٌ لِمَا تَشَآءُ \nO You! Who are readily pleased, forgive one who owes nothing but prayers, verily You does what You will.\nيَا مَنِ اسْمُهٗ دَوَآءٌ وَ ذِكْرُهٗ شِفَآءٌ وَ طَاعَتُهٗ غِنًى \nO You! Whose name is the remedy (for all ills) and whose Remembrance is a sure cure for all ailments, and whose obedience will make one independent of all, \nاِرْحَمْ مَنْ رَأْسُ مَالِهِ الرَّجَآءُ وَ سِلَاحُهُ الْبُكَآءُ \nhave Mercy on one whose only asset is his hope (in Your Kindness and Mercy) and whose only armament is supplication to You.\nيَا سَابِـغَ النِّعَمِ يَا دَافِعَ النِّقَمِ يَا نُوْرَ الْمُسْتَوْحِشِيْنَ فِي الظُّلَمِ \nO You! Who bestoweth cure and happiness, who granteth remedy and blessings and who wardeth off misfortunes, O Light Who illuminateth those who are in darkness (of sins and sorrows), \nيَا عَالِمًا لَّا يُعَلَّمُ صَلِّ عَلٰى مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ آلِ مُحَمَّدٍ \nO Omniscient! Who knows without (acquisition of) learning, bless Muhammad and descendant’s of Muhammad \nوَّ افْعَلْ بِيْ مَا اَنْتَ اَهْلُهٗ وَ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلٰى رَسُوْلِهٖ \nand do that unto me which befitts You (Your Mercy, Kindness and Grace). And my Lord! bless Muhammad and the blessed leaders amongst his descendants \nوَ اْلَائِمَّةِ الْمَيَامِيْنَ مِنْ آلِهِ وَ سَلَّمَ تَسْلِيْمًا كَثِيْرًا.\nand bestow upon them peace and tranquility to the utmost extent that You can.", 
    "title": "Dua Kumayl"
}